main event: On the evening of 23 August 1966, Mr. and Mrs. A observed a circular object, initially seen as one, later observed as five objects, which maneuvered silently before disappearing after approximately 15 minutes.
interesting points: The initial object appeared silvery metallic and had an inner luminous area surrounded by a halo of light., The objects maneuvered silently without any sounds or trails., Mr. A found a sticky residue on his binoculars after the sighting., The sighting was discussed in the context of reaching out to local newspapers for further witness reports., The objects were not identifiable as any known aircraft or aerial phenomena.
sighted object: one circular object which became five separate objects
witness description: Mr. and Mrs. A described as normal, sensible people
